---
title: Quickstart
description: Get up and running with Nightshift in minutes
---

## Install the toolchain

After building Nightshift, install the tools to a prefix:

```bash
./dist/nightshift-<os>-<arch>/bin/nightshift install --prefix ~/.nightshift
```

This downloads and installs:
- OpenCode
- Python 3.13
- uv (Python package manager)
- ripgrep

## Launch the TUI

Start Nightshift with the built-in TUI:

```bash
./dist/nightshift-<os>-<arch>/bin/nightshift run --prefix ~/.nightshift --run-nightshift-tui
```

This starts OpenCode in server mode and attaches the Nightshift TUI.

## Run OpenCode directly

If you prefer the default OpenCode interface:

```bash
./dist/nightshift-<os>-<arch>/bin/nightshift run --prefix ~/.nightshift
```

Pass extra arguments to OpenCode with `--`:

```bash
./dist/nightshift-<os>-<arch>/bin/nightshift run --prefix ~/.nightshift -- --continue
```
